timeEvent.name: Wedding
timeEvent.description: The first wedding in your community took place on Sunday Afternoon.Both bride and groom came to Woolwich over 3 years ago.After the ceremony the bridal party returned to their home, were breakfast and dinner were served and dancing engaged in.

timeEvent.name: Arrival
timeEvent.description: You have arrived in the town of Woolwich, on the outskirts of London, England. It has been a long journey and you are far from home. You need to find a place to stay and settle for awhile in this new place.

timeEvent.name: Arsenal Football team moves
timeEvent.description: Now a professional football team, the Arsenal team started by workers at the Gunners factory at the Arsenal moves to Highbury, North London.

timeEvent.name: Haleys Comet
timeEvent.description: The Great Daylight Comet is sighted in the skies over London. Warning to the Inhabitants of the City: Close your windows and keep indoors for the Earth will soon pass through the Tail of the terrible Comet and its poisonous gases will fill the heavens!

timeEvent.name: Jobs For Women at the Arsenal!
timeEvent.description: Since 1872 women had been banned from working in the Arsenal, but with the start of WW1 all our boys are going to war. For the duration of the war women munitions workers are required.

timeEvent.name: Houses for 6 pounds a week
timeEvent.description: Cheap housing is available for newcomers to Woolwich, some local shops, some rundown cottages near Dairy Lane and Frances Street. Take care of the vagrants and overcrowding in this area.

timeEvent.name: Wellington Cottages
timeEvent.description: The local policemen have moved into this area and it is therefore regarded as a safe place to live.

timeEvent.name: Jobs Available in the Arsenal
timeEvent.description: Jobs are available at the Arsenal for the men in your community. Houses are available for the Arsenal workers in Plumstead and near the common. Beware temptation in the many public houses. It is an eight hour day and overtime to be had.

timeEvent.name: Jobs Available In The Arsenal
timeEvent.description: Jobs are available at the Arsenal for the men in your community. Houses are available for the Arsenal workers in Plumstead and near the common. Beware temptation in the many public houses. It is an eight hour day and overtime to be had.

timeEvent.name: The last day of buses through the market
timeEvent.description: Finally after decades of complaints about traffic through the market, buses have stopped driving through the market. Some say this has effected the character of the market

timeEvent.name: Prince Charles visits Beresford Square Market
timeEvent.description: Prince of Wales arrives by car to the crowded market square. He steps from the car, greets waiting officials, and shakes hands. Shot from above, the Prince proceeds through the crowded market, escorted by policemen some mounted. The Prince makes his way to the car through a jostling crowd.

timeEvent.name: Prince Charles visits Beresford Square Market
timeEvent.description: Prince of Wales arrives by car to the crowded market square. He steps from the car, greets waiting officials, and shakes hands. Shot from above, the Prince proceeds through the crowded market, escorted by policemen some mounted. The Prince makes his way to the car through a jostling crowd.

timeEvent.name: 36 ton boiler falls off a lorry
timeEvent.description: A huge 36 ton boiler, as a big house fell off a lorry and crashed into an off licence, luckily no one was injured but alot of damage was caused along the High Street.

timeEvent.name: Fire in the Marshes likely to burn for a month!
timeEvent.description: A fire started on the side of the rail track which is likely to burn for a month

timeEvent.name: Queen Mary Comes to Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Queen Mary visits Woolwich, she meets mothers and babies, and nurses as part of the war effort.

timeEvent.name: King George V visits the Barracks
timeEvent.description: The King inspects the Royal Regiment of Artillery... from week-old recruits to fully trained gunner!"

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Boys Make Canoes
timeEvent.description: Woolwich Recreational Institute starts carpentry lessons for teenage boys - building canoes. Boys aged between 16 and 21 using hammers hand drills and saws to build the canoes and then paint them and then they go canoing at Danson Park Lake... Sights like these are a glowing tribute to the much maligned youth of today

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Polytechnic Old Boys Association Reformed
timeEvent.description: Meetings and dances taking place at the Poly or at the Town Hall. Community spirit being much to the fore with chess, debating, drama, Ping-pong (sic), swimming and tennis featuring as well as football and cricket.

timeEvent.name: War Memorial Funding a clubhouse
timeEvent.description: The War Memorial Fund has purchased a house at 72 Footscray Road which was turned into a clubhouse, including a much needed bar, for the Old Shootershillian Association

timeEvent.name: Shooters Hill C C are formed
timeEvent.description: Old Shootershillian Association are now Shooters Hill CC Rugby team, playing in the Kent League.

timeEvent.name: Britain's Christmas Stocking
timeEvent.description: The barracks prepare Christmas Puddings to give out to the Army

timeEvent.name: Couple's cooking classes for married and engaged couples!
timeEvent.description: Cookery classes are available to help both husbands and wife in Woolwich to cook properly.. to break down the old notion that 'indigestion is the cause of wrecked marriages'. Men may find this is the thin end of the wedge.

timeEvent.name: Prince Albert the Duke of York visits to watch army football
timeEvent.description: Duke of York sees British Army score runaway win by 6 goals to 2 over Belgian Army.

timeEvent.name: Midsummer Night's Dream performed at the Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: The munitions worker's nursery is performing Midsummer's Night Dream

timeEvent.name: Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: Nursery opened up in Deptford that mainly with places for munitions workers. The nursery provides a strong emphasis on playing, learning and sleeping outside.

timeEvent.name: Midsummer Night's Dream performed at the Rachel McMillan Nursery School
timeEvent.description: The munitions worker's nursery is performing Midsummer's Night Dream

timeEvent.name: London Suffragette Pageant
timeEvent.description: 66,000 women make a procession through London. By taking their campaign to the streets, the Women's Social and Political Union attract maximum publicity. Identifiable by their purple, white and green colour scheme, the suffragettes are becoming a familiar sight in central London.

timeEvent.name: Folk Club nights taking place
timeEvent.description: Folk clubs are like dog fighting clubs, they're often little known about

timeEvent.name: A big cat spotted in Thamesmead!
timeEvent.description: A black leopard like creature is believed to have been spotted in Thamesmead. The sighting happened at around 3am on Saturday morning (August 9) in Goldfinch Road when a man was woken up by something screeching. The man, who did not want to be named, said: "I saw a black animal rolling on the grass between two trees. I thought to myself, 'Bloody hell! That's the biggest moggy I've ever seen', and then thought, 'It must be a dog'. However, its head was cat-like and its tail was very long.

timeEvent.name: MC Afrikan Boy filmed in Woolwich by Spike Jonze
timeEvent.description: Spike Jonze and M.I.A. visit MC Afrikan Boy on his council estate in Woolwich. Yes that's right, the director of Being John Malcovich and Beastie Boys videos was up a tower block in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: Afirkan Boy is born
timeEvent.description: Olushola Ajose, better known by his stage name "Afrikan Boy" born 28 March 1989 is a grime/Afrobeat MC from Woolwich, London, England, originally from Nigeria.

timeEvent.name: The Biafran War
timeEvent.description: The Biafran war, 1967-1970, resulted in 100,000 military casualties. However, between 500,000 and 2 million Biafran civilians died from starvation during the war. Many Biafrans move to Woolwich to escape the war and find a new home

timeEvent.name: Teenagers hang out at the Dockyard
timeEvent.description: Saturday nights at Woolwich Dockyard teenagers come and hang out.

timeEvent.name: Red Magnets appear in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A communist theatre group starts in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: The Empire Theatre renamed
timeEvent.description: Woolwich's Theatre is renamed the Woolwich Empire with a capacity of 1,450 seats.

timeEvent.name: Teddy Boy Trouble
timeEvent.description: Police were called to the cinema's around London last night to deal with disturbances among youthful audiences during showings of the film ‘Rock Around the Clock’... 30 policemen arrived. One was knocked between two rows of seats when he tried to stop the dancing. Police and commissionaires ejected about 50 youths. Six youths will appear in court at Woolwich SE today, charged with insulting behaviour outside the Granada cinema, Woolwich, where the film had been shown’.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich women in song
timeEvent.description: 'She works at Woolwich Arsenal Now' - a munition worker's romance' is released

timeEvent.name: New Woolwich Ferry Terminal
timeEvent.description: New terminal for the ferry for cars and lorries

timeEvent.name: Gypsy Moth IV Yacht leaves Woolwich
timeEvent.description: 'Gipsy Moth IV' travels from Woolwich to be permanently berthed at Greenwich, London.

timeEvent.name: New Prefabs in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Prisoners of war are being brought in to build prefab houses needed as a result of bombed out houses and returning service men to solve the housing crisis, in 10 weeks something like a little suburb will be erected and slotted into place

timeEvent.name: The last London tram leaves from Woolwich
timeEvent.description: A special tram was driven through enormous crowds from Woolwich to New Cross, finally arriving at New Cross depot around 1am on the 6 July.

timeEvent.name: The first MacDonalds in Britain Opens
timeEvent.description: The first ever MacDonalds to open in Britain opens on Powis Street. Woolwich was chosen because it was considered to be a representative English town at the time.

timeEvent.name: Children of Men filmed in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: The apocalypic British film Children of Men was filmed partly in Woolwich.

timeEvent.name: The Woolwich Arsenal finally closes!
timeEvent.description: Th Arsenal finally closes after a long decline.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich Arsenal Station Opens
timeEvent.description: The new terminus of the Docklands Light Railway's London City Airport branch, Woolwich Arsenal station, opened on 10 January 2009.

timeEvent.name: The Royal Military Academy has closed
timeEvent.description: Known as the Shop, the RMA has closed down, taking the jobs with it.

timeEvent.name: Games and holidays stopped at The Shop
timeEvent.description: Due to the war the Royal Military Academy has stopped all sports, games and holidays

timeEvent.name: 860 gunner cadets join The Shop
timeEvent.description: 860 new gunner cadets are recruited to the Royal Military Academy

timeEvent.name: 860 cadets killed in the war
timeEvent.description: 860 cadets have been killed in the war, coincidently the same number as the amount of new cadets that joined the Royal Military Academy in 1916.578 were gunners from the new recruits.

timeEvent.name: Woolwich artillery theatre has burned down
Woolwich Artillery theatre rebuilt
timeEvent.description: Woolwich artillery theatre rebuilt, patrionised increasingly by local townspeople

timeEvent.name: Royal Artillery Bands Training Starts
timeEvent.description: The Bandboys Troop for the military and musical training for Royal Artillary Bands

timeEvent.name: Junior Artillery Band Starts
timeEvent.description: Junior Musicians Troop Artillery Band was established

timeEvent.name: A new stadium opens of Woolwich Common
timeEvent.description: The stadium on Woolwich Common established as a general sports stadium

timeEvent.name: The First Searchlight Tattoo takes Place
The first Police Station Opens in Woolwich
timeEvent.description: The first police station in Woolwich opens, before then the town has been policed by the Arsenal

timeEvent.name: Jobs are very scarce in Woolwich
Night raids on the Arsenal
timeEvent.description: Night raids by Zeppelins and bombs dropped on artillery place, front parade ground and Mill Lane

timeEvent.name: Night raids
timeEvent.description: Night raids by Zeppelins and bombs dropped on artillery place, front parade ground and Mill Lane

timeEvent.name: Casualties caused by night raids on the Arsenal and Royal Military Academy
Bombs on Woolwich
timeEvent.description: Garrison Church lost its stained glass windows

The Arsenal Closes
timeEvent.description: The Arsenal closes, many engineering companies also close that provided jobs and services to the Arsenal

timeEvent.name: Stephen Lawrence stabbed to death
timeEvent.description: Stephen Lawrence who lived and grew up on the Nightingale Estate in Woolwich is stabbed in Eltham.

timeEvent.name: A report occurs about the bad health of the Thames
Motorbikes supplied to the US
timeEvent.description: Share capital doubles of motorbike industry in Woolwich and jobs increase

timeEvent.name: Motorbikes are no longer made in Woolwich
Ferry carrying 20,000 passengers
timeEvent.description: Every day 20,000 passengers travel on the Woolwich ferry across the Thames to jobs and bringing people to work in Woolwich

timeEvent.name: Woolwich centre a good place to live
timeEvent.description: The city streets look comfortable and safe, people's steps shine white

timeEvent.name: Arsenal workers live in Plumstead
timeEvent.description: many of the workers at the Arsenal live in Plumstead, their wives earn money doing washing and their daughters doing piece work

timeEvent.name: Explosions on the marshes
timeEvent.description: Occassional explosions taking place on the marshes, followed by crashes often make the windows shake as far as Shooters Hill. Sometimes windows break but you cant get compensation from the government

timeEvent.name: Jobs at the Theatre
timeEvent.description: The theatre in Pumstead is one of the main employers outside the Arsenal

timeEvent.name: Bob Hope is born in Eltham
New homes available
timeEvent.description: new homes are available for newly married couples and young families

timeEvent.name: Popular music Hall in Beresford Street
timeEvent.description: The music hall in Beresford Street is very popual with 14-18 year olds from around Woolwich coming to watch musicals such as Drummed Out a parody of working at the Arsenal.

timeEvent.name: The woods are like countryside
timeEvent.description: If you take a walk in the woods beyond the common you can find pheasants and bluebells and nightingale's singing
